node.text:
Full edit from yesterday’s post. Level 1 Constructions did work at the 2013 Orage Masters in Sun Valley, ID. Some traffic control, double front cone bonks, 2000 feet of caution tape, smoke breaks, more than a few beers, and triple back flips, all in a days work. After a long day on the job our crew of Mike Hornbeck (foreman), Chris Logan, LJ Strenio, and Banks Gilberti walked away with the win. Contact our union rep to file any complaints or grievances.

@dahrkgram @mike_hornbeck @banks.gilberti @ljstrenio

Where you at @denverpolice ???

We found the name of the suspect, where she was living, got statements from her neighbors noting a history of violence, and found the Bronco half spray painted in a poor attempt to conceal it.

@howjoshisliving  made 15 calls to the detective assigned to the case (aggregated assault, hit and run, grand larceny), a few more calls to the supervising sergeant, and many more to the Denver District One station without a single call back or followup.  @seandubois1 whose bike was stolen was told that the detective assigned to his separate case “was on vacation for the next few weeks.”

#Denver should do better than this. @mayorhancock 

Broadcast from @fox31denver

node.text:
@mike_hornbeck is the working man’s skier. After 6 years skiing in the Level 1 crew, Wrecka’s unmistakable greasy style and tireless work ethic paid off with this part in 2012. From spot selection to trick choice, Hornbeck’s opening segment from Sunny is timeless.

#Level1Archive

Hot off his SuperUnknown win, @skimanguy came out swinging for our 2014 feature film “Less”. The result was a banger part with an extremely memorable ender. The direction Magnus has taken his style in since then only makes this seg sweeter - whether it’s swerve skiing or old-school stee, we back it all. More on the way from the #Level1Archive all summer long.
A classic from the vault. @ahmetdadali slaying pow and street in one of the most memorable Level 1 segments of all time. Stay tuned for more #Level1Archive drops all summer long.

We wanted to do a little more for all those who submitted entries to SuperUnknown this year so we went back through the entries, collected all of our favorite tricks and put them together in this city for you to watch and pick your favorites.

We’re giving away $500 cash + $250 @sagaouterwear gift card to the winner, along with another $250 gift card awarded to one randomly chosen voter!  Every vote you cast enters you for your chance to win.

Link in bio to vote! @newschoolers @ikonpass 

@vu_vilma @till_i_break_it @seamus_flanagan @a11_memento @isabella_tvede @samuelalander @gtbalen @bsee.z @oski.toboggan @young__snow @_bennie @kylecoxworth @gucci_logan @cattylou3 @rynknndy @enric_fnt @faib_this_way @bellla.bacon @bleevus @salutmoicestraf

The wait is over - the winners are here! Our fourth and final video recap from SuperUnknown Finals is live, and it's a doozy.  Tune in to watch the crew get creative on a rainbow to banana-bars feature, and a lively session on a Kimbo up-rail that Woodward Eldora park crew nailed the setup on. 

Featuring the whole damn crew:  @oski.toboggan @young__snow @kylecoxworth @bsee.z @_bennie @masonkennedy @dmtheactivist @lukeobrien3 @erectile_chrisfunction @seamus_flanagan @bellla.bacon @skyeclarkee @cattylou3 @i.go.hamill 

SuperUnknown has been presented by @woodward__eldora @ikonpass @sagaouterwear @newschoolers

Days 2 and 3 of SuperUnknown Finals saw the fog roll in, and the crew delivered heat amidst the gnarliest week of weather we have ever had at a Finals event.  The Woodward Eldora park crew tee'd up some nasty challenge rails, including a Quad Kink with a 30-foot downrail at the end, and an Elbow to DFD that the athletes got slimy on. Watch @_bennie @bellla.bacon @cattylou3 @bsee.z @oski.toboggan  @kylecoxworth @masonkennedy @skyeclarkee @mcbskee @erectile_chrisfunction @i.go.hamill @dmtheactivist @young__snow @lukeobrien3 @seamus_flanagan throw down- also available on YouTube to watch on a big screen!

For the sixth installment of our classic Mile-Hi hoodie series we’re bringing the pullover back in new colors. Once again the custom cut-and-sew construction includes just a little extra length and a slimmer-fitting waist. This hoodie comes with a zippered media pocket inside the pouch. Perfectly sized to securely fit an iPhone 12 or whatever else you want to put in there. As always, we included some extra embroidery detailing, custom tagging, and flat hood-cinch lacing. Super comfy 10oz 50/50 cotton/poly blend holds shape and stays soft! #merchandise #hoodies
